
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-francois-ipv6-dots-signal-option-00.txt'>
    <title>"IPv6 DOTS Signal Option", Jerome Francois, Abdelkader Lahmadi, Giovane Moura, Marco Davids</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-francois-ipv6-dots-signal-option-00.txt</link>
    <description>This document describes a delivery mechanism based on the IPv6 Hop- by-Hop options extension header type to carry a DOTS client signal message over a congested network due to a DDoS attack. The specified mechanism allows the DOTS client signal message to be included using an opportunistic way in outgoing IPv6 packets traveling then through the network to reach a DOTS server or relay.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-03-21T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
